overview: The user initiated a task to enhance a sleep questionnaire application
  by adding database functionality and an admin dashboard, based on a provided
  Statement of Work. The assistant first evaluated the existing codebase,
  identifying that while the questionnaire logic and PDF generation were in
  place, database storage, data retrieval (CSV), an admin dashboard, and
  authentication were missing. After clarifying the desired authentication
  complexity (simple password) and demographic data fields (combining SOW and
  existing fields), a comprehensive plan was developed. The implementation
  involved updating demographic types and form fields, creating a Prisma model
  for questionnaire responses, developing API endpoints for saving and
  retrieving data (including CSV export), and building a simple
  password-protected admin dashboard with login and logout functionalities. The
  questionnaire form was also updated to submit data to the new database. NeonDB
  was chosen for the database, aligning with the user's preference and Prisma's
  PostgreSQL support.
